{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"circuit-program","item_id":"i-priv003","details":{"description":"PRIV-003 (older open)","context":"Branch: \"Circuit bug program\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"PRIV-003 is a privacy-class bug surfaced by the audit-vocabulary / security sweep. The bug ID prefix follows the Circuit `<TAG>-NNN` finding-id convention. Look up the finding row in `docs/findings.md` (Circuit project) or the originating review doc to see the file:line, severity, and recommended fix.","options":null,"recommendation":"Don't ship a privacy fix without an explicit Misha decision — these usually touch user-data surfaces and warrant a Tier-2+ decision record per `~/.claude/rules/planning.md`.","blocking_input":"Either schedule the fix (open a worktree, run the recommended remediation) or defer to a future privacy-cluster sweep. If unsure of the source row, ask Claude to grep `docs/findings.md` for `PRIV-003`.","links":["(see branch: Circuit bug program)","docs/findings.md (Circuit — grep for `PRIV-003`)"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCPDRF2AM9JR7RHMCHHW","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.557Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"circuit-program","item_id":"i-a11y001","details":{"description":"A11Y-001 (older open)","context":"Branch: \"Circuit bug program\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"A11Y-001 is an accessibility-class bug surfaced by the UX/audience audit pass. The Circuit `<TAG>-NNN` convention: look up the row in `docs/findings.md` or `docs/reviews/2026-05-13-ux-audit.md` for the file:line + recommended fix (typically a missing ARIA label, focus ring, or keyboard nav).","options":null,"recommendation":"Bundle with sibling a11y findings in a single sweep PR — A11Y-001 is rarely an isolated issue, and the audit usually surfaces a cluster.","blocking_input":"Schedule the fix or defer. A11Y fixes are usually small (one or two attribute changes) and ship safely without an ADR.","links":["(see branch: Circuit bug program)","docs/reviews/2026-05-13-ux-audit.md"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCPWQ6NJG7FRP0PA4GCR","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.572Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"circuit-program","item_id":"i-journey009","details":{"description":"JOURNEY-009 (older open)","context":"Branch: \"Circuit bug program\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"JOURNEY-009 — Retell/voice setup signal — flagged P1 in `docs/reviews/circuit-onboarding-robustness-audit-2026-05-17.md`. Per Misha's prior call (backlog entry, 2026-05-17): kept OPEN, NOT auto-fixed, because 'fixing as a mandatory banner would recreate the JOURNEY-024 false-universal mistake; voice/AI is opt-in like ServiceTitan'. Decision needed: design a context-sensitive signal (only-when-relevant) OR leave dormant.","options":null,"recommendation":"Leave dormant. The current call (kept open, not auto-fixed) is correct — premature signaling re-creates the JOURNEY-024 'false-universal' bug. Revisit only when a contractor surfaces the friction.","blocking_input":"Product-direction call from Misha: design the context-sensitive signal now, or leave dormant until voice/AI adoption surfaces real friction.","links":["docs/reviews/circuit-onboarding-robustness-audit-2026-05-17.md","(see branch: Circuit bug program)"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCQ698KW7N9PXQZ21RQP","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.582Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"circuit-program","item_id":"i-journey023","details":{"description":"JOURNEY-023 (older open)","context":"Branch: \"Circuit bug program\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"JOURNEY-023 — onboarding-wizard developer-jargon content cluster (Grade D in §2/§7 of the audit). Entangled with the unmerged 2026-05-16 design-doc branch `claude/gifted-pasteur-d193a2`. Per Misha's prior call: surfaced, NOT auto-fixed — audit explicitly says 'don't relitigate product direction'. Decision needed: either merge `claude/gifted-pasteur-d193a2` (which carries the F5-redesign copy) OR pull the copy fixes into a smaller standalone PR.","options":null,"recommendation":"Path (a) if the redesign is otherwise ready; path (b) if the redesign needs more iteration. VOCAB-002 also lives in this cluster — wizard 'API Password' for Twilio token is still on the new wizard component.","blocking_input":"Either: (a) sign off on `claude/gifted-pasteur-d193a2` so the redesign merges; or (b) ask Claude to extract the JOURNEY-023 copy-only fixes into a standalone PR.","links":["docs/reviews/circuit-onboarding-robustness-audit-2026-05-17.md","docs/reviews/circuit-audience-vocabulary-audit-2026-05-17.md","(see branch: Circuit bug program)"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCQHMP1B8SKR0D376ZJR","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.593Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"onboarding-demo","item_id":"i-resend","details":{"description":"RESEND_FROM_EMAIL + DKIM","context":"Branch: \"Onboarding — contractor demo (tomorrow)\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"Demo prerequisite: confirm `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` is set in Vercel prod env AND the corresponding DKIM record is published on the sending domain. Without DKIM, transactional emails (invitations, password resets) land in spam and the demo's white-glove invitation flow looks broken. Verify by sending a test invite to a personal email and checking inbox vs. spam + headers (DKIM=pass).","options":null,"recommendation":"Do this in the same sitting as the A2P portal paste — both are pre-demo prerequisites involving external consoles.","blocking_input":"Misha-only: log into Vercel + DNS provider to verify/set. Cannot be done by Claude.","links":["(see branch: Onboarding — contractor demo (tomorrow))","docs/contractor-onboarding-walkthrough-runbook-2026-05-17.md"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCQX97XHWZJEDQZV1BKM","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.605Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"onboarding-demo","item_id":"i-supabase","details":{"description":"npx supabase db push (migration 137)","context":"Branch: \"Onboarding — contractor demo (tomorrow)\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"Run `npx supabase db push` to apply migration 137 (`messages.external_id UNIQUE` per the WHK-001 idempotency fix). This was already pushed for the production org per the 2026-05-18 backlog entry — but if the demo org is on a different Supabase project, re-run there. Verify after: query `SELECT conname FROM pg_constraint WHERE conrelid = 'messages'::regclass AND contype='u';` — should show the UNIQUE constraint on external_id.","options":null,"recommendation":"Confirm first: is the demo org on the prod Supabase project? If yes, the migration already shipped (per backlog 2026-05-18 entry) — mark complete. If no, push to the other project.","blocking_input":"Misha-only: needs Supabase CLI auth to the target project. If the demo org is on prod (single Supabase project per the backlog note), it's already done and this item can be marked complete.","links":["docs/twilio-integration-e2e-test-2026-05-17.md (migration 137 = messages.external_id UNIQUE, WHK-001 fix)","(see branch: Onboarding — contractor demo (tomorrow))"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCR9D7QM72TAJFP4WB6A","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.617Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"pricing-structure","item_id":"i-pricing","details":{"description":"Pricing structure conversation — before tomorrow","context":"Branch: \"Pricing structure conversation\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"INTERACTIVE CONVERSATION needed — Misha + Claude. No source doc exists yet because no decisions have been made. Topics to cover when ready: (1) tier definitions (Free / Pro / Enterprise — or different shape?); (2) per-tier feature gating (what's a tier vs an add-on?); (3) usage-based dimensions (per-org, per-conversation, per-message, per-AI-call?); (4) launch pricing vs. early-adopter pricing; (5) annual vs monthly discount shape; (6) public-page rollout (landing page, /pricing route, marketing assets).","options":null,"recommendation":"Block ~60–90 min for a focused conversation. Bring competitive landscape (ServiceTitan/Housecall Pro pricing pages) and a sense of the contractor's willingness-to-pay (from white-glove conversations).","blocking_input":"Misha schedules an interactive Dispatch session to think through the structure. Until that happens, all downstream pricing work (landing page copy, billing integration, /pricing route) is blocked.","links":["(see branch: Pricing structure conversation)","docs/backlog.md (the 'Pricing structure conversation' backlog entry tracks this)"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCRN7Q52H28R032MDQMG","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.629Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"circuit-p6","item_id":"i-tcpa","details":{"description":"TCPA: 8 decision cards — docs/reviews/tcpa-decision-options-2026-05-17.md","context":"Branch: \"Phase 6 plan — preventive controls (DRAFT, needs Misha review)\" (open). Sourced from docs/reviews/tcpa-decision-options-2026-05-17.md § \"TCPA-001 — Quiet-hours computed against the wrong timezone on every SMS send\".","instructions":"Open `docs/reviews/tcpa-decision-options-2026-05-17.md` — 8 decision cards (TCPA-001 through TCPA-007 + TCPA-009). For each card, either pick A/B/C OR approve the drafted copy verbatim OR edit inline. The 'What you need from Misha to ship' line on each card is the single blocking input. Once all 8 are decided, the obvious-fix sweep ships them in one PR.","options":[{"label":"TCPA-001 — Quiet-hours TZ source","pros":"A=Zip→IANA + NPA fallback (recommended; strongest legal posture, data already on contact); B=NPA only (smallest impl); C=stored contacts.timezone col + backfill (most auditable, biggest migration)","cons":"A=zip→TZ table needs bundling ~400KB; B=number portability means wrong-TZ sends still possible; C=requires shared-prod migration"},{"label":"TCPA-001 fail-closed policy","pros":"BLOCK marketing when TZ unresolved (recommended); transactional still sends"},{"label":"TCPA-002 — Scheduled sends use recipient TZ, not org TZ (decide together with TCPA-001)"},{"label":"TCPA-003..006 (+ P1s TCPA-007, TCPA-009)","pros":"See cards in the doc — each has 3 options + recommendation + drafted copy"}],"recommendation":"Read the doc once end-to-end, decide all 8 in one sitting, hand back. The sweep PR is already specced — only the policy choices block it.","blocking_input":"8 A/B/C decisions from Misha + sign-off on drafted copy for TCPA-007 (HELP/STOP) and TCPA-009. Legal-claim honesty: $500–$1,500/text under 47 U.S.C. § 227(b)(3); quiet-hours-applied-to-SMS is plaintiff practice [verify with counsel] for exact theory.","links":["docs/reviews/tcpa-decision-options-2026-05-17.md","docs/reviews/circuit-tcpa-sms-compliance-audit-2026-05-17.md"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCS2QRN2HXT3T45GV9N6","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.642Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"circuit-p6","item_id":"i-p6-ratify","details":{"description":"Phase 6 plan ratification — docs/plans/phase-6-preventive-controls.md","context":"Branch: \"Phase 6 plan — preventive controls (DRAFT, needs Misha review)\" (open). Sourced from docs/plans/phase-6-preventive-controls.md § \"Files to Modify/Create (Phase-6 build — NOT this session)\".","instructions":"Open `docs/plans/phase-6-preventive-controls.md` (Status: DRAFT). Read the Goal + Scope + Why-now sections. The plan unifies three preventive layers: (A) per-org cost/rate ceiling — fail-closed BEFORE spend, not after; (B) error-spine alerter — push critical `system_errors` to a human; (C) `webhook_events` dedup ledger — structural at-least-once replay protection. Hard dependency: PR #249 (`claude/admiring-mcnulty-f1c358`) must merge to master first — Phase-6 builds on top of it. Once Misha ratifies, flip Status DRAFT → ACTIVE and the build can begin.","options":null,"recommendation":"Don't ratify until PR #249 lands (the plan has a hard build-on dependency). Ratifying earlier risks the foundation moving under the plan.","blocking_input":"Misha-only: read the plan, decide whether to ratify as-written, request changes, or split into smaller phases. The 'open questions' section at the bottom of the plan lists specific unresolved items needing input.","links":["docs/plans/phase-6-preventive-controls.md","docs/reviews/circuit-phase5-consolidated-rollup-2026-05-17.md"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCSFTY897XTF36P08JPM","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.655Z","actor":"dispatch"}
