{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"a2p-portal","item_id":"i-a2p-paste","details":{"description":"A2P portal paste — Blocks A–F (paste-ready)","context":"Branch: \"Manual portal actions — paste-ready (waiting on Misha)\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"Open the Twilio Console (SSO) and execute Steps 1–6 of `docs/twilio-a2p-manual-actions-misha-2026-05-17.md`: (1) Confirm the A2P Brand is APPROVED, note the TCR Brand ID + Trust Score; (2) Submit/refresh the Campaign (the §1 CTA hard-blocker is already cleared on prod — `/sms-terms`, `/api/request-service`, `/privacy`, `/terms` all live & green); (3) Associate the messaging service to the campaign; (4) Confirm the long code is registered under that campaign; (5) Verify by sending one test SMS via the Twilio console; (6) Update the org's `twilio_config.account_sid` if it changed during registration. All paste-ready copy + paste targets are in the doc.","options":null,"recommendation":"Execute in order — each step depends on the previous one. Total elapsed: ~30–45 min if Brand is already APPROVED, longer if Brand is PENDING (then you wait for Twilio, not for execution).","blocking_input":"Misha-only: Twilio Console SSO is required for every step. None of this can be done by Claude.","links":["docs/twilio-a2p-manual-actions-misha-2026-05-17.md","docs/twilio-a2p-10dlc-registration-guide.md"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCW4AS5W9CXFMMXBYG07","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.740Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"type":"item-details-set","node_id":"twilio-twlo006","item_id":"i-twlo006","details":{"description":"Wire demo org's twilio_config (launch-blocker)","context":"Branch: \"TWLO-006 launch-blocker — wire demo org twilio_config (waiting on Misha)\" (open) — a tracked Dispatch conversation. Full source detail lives in the linked Dispatch doc (not in the tracker state).","instructions":"On the demo / onboarded org set `twilio_config.phone_number=\"+19493905976\"` AND align `twilio_config.account_sid` + per-org Vault `twilio_auth_token` to the active Twilio account (last-4 `…66c9`). The inbound signature check uses global `process.env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`, so the owning org's account MUST match that env token (TWLO-004). Until this lands, `handleInboundSms` returns `org_not_found` → silent empty-TwiML 200, and every real inbound SMS (replies/STOP/HELP/AI) is dropped regardless of TWLO-001.","options":null,"recommendation":"Do this BEFORE the demo. Without it the demo's inbound SMS path is silently broken — no error, just empty 200s and no AI replies.","blocking_input":"Launch-blocker for tomorrow's demo. No code change — Misha needs to update the demo org's `twilio_config` row in Supabase prod (`organizations.twilio_config->>phone_number = +19493905976`).","links":["docs/backlog.md (P0 section, TWLO-006 entry)","(see branch: TWLO-006 launch-blocker — wire demo org twilio_config (waiting on Misha))"]},"event_id":"01KS3JFCWGESYZBXQBHQM7HR5T","ts":"2026-05-20T20:50:44.752Z","actor":"dispatch"}
{"event_id":"cte-bo-5bd34ea32830aaffe5d492240305f9f7","type":"branch-opened","node_id":"observability-signup","parent_id":"root-sprint","title":"Observability — Sentry + Axiom signup","actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:04:50.148Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-action-b8bcd83503f4f2e14812f5953ec6145e","type":"action-added","node_id":"observability-signup","item_id":"i-sentry-signup","text":"Sign up for Sentry — paste back DSN, auth-token, org & project slugs","actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:04:52.264Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-detset-b8bcd83503f4f2e14812f5953ec6145e","type":"item-details-set","node_id":"observability-signup","item_id":"i-sentry-signup","details":{"description":"Sentry is the proposed error-tracking backend for the customer-facing app. Orchestrator cannot provision the account; needs Misha to register and return the credentials so the integration can be wired.","instructions":"1) Create a Sentry account (or use an existing one) at sentry.io. 2) Create a new project for the customer-facing app (TypeScript/Next.js). 3) Copy: (a) the DSN, (b) an auth-token with project:write + project:read scopes (Settings → Auth Tokens → Create New), (c) the organization slug, (d) the project slug. 4) Paste all four back in a Dispatch reply.","recommendation":"Use the Team plan if you anticipate >5k events/month; Developer plan is fine for the launch sprint.","blocking_input":"Sentry DSN + auth-token + org slug + project slug","links":["(see branch: Observability — Sentry + Axiom signup)"]},"actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:04:52.280Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-action-8248e5430b8b92eadd55cb7076d6c7ad","type":"action-added","node_id":"observability-signup","item_id":"i-axiom-signup","text":"Sign up for Axiom — paste back ingest token","actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:04:54.390Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-detset-8248e5430b8b92eadd55cb7076d6c7ad","type":"item-details-set","node_id":"observability-signup","item_id":"i-axiom-signup","details":{"description":"Axiom is the proposed structured-log backend (paired with Sentry for errors). Orchestrator needs an ingest token to wire the log shipper.","instructions":"1) Create an Axiom account at axiom.co. 2) Create a dataset (suggest: customer-app-prod). 3) Generate an API token with ingest permission on that dataset (Settings → API Tokens). 4) Paste the token + dataset name back in a Dispatch reply.","recommendation":"Free tier covers up to 500GB/month — comfortable for launch + first 90 days.","blocking_input":"Axiom ingest token + dataset name","links":["(see branch: Observability — Sentry + Axiom signup)"]},"actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:04:54.410Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-bo-9120aab814b2f5e547d19e301c7dd1ea","type":"branch-opened","node_id":"vercel-migration","parent_id":"root-sprint","title":"Vercel migration / hosted-routes decision","actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:05:44.275Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-decisi-490453184ed31bae49b35fa91c0ac55b","type":"decision-raised","node_id":"vercel-migration","item_id":"i-vercel-approach","text":"Choose between (a) bisect, (b) hosted-routes-only, (c) full Vercel migration","actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:05:46.337Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-detset-490453184ed31bae49b35fa91c0ac55b","type":"item-details-set","node_id":"vercel-migration","item_id":"i-vercel-approach","details":{"description":"The customer-app's hosting story has three credible paths forward. Each carries a different blast-radius + reversibility tradeoff. Decision is needed before the Vercel-migration comparison work can start.","options":[{"label":"(a) Bisect the current deploy issue first","pros":"Cheapest; isolates the actual root cause; doesn't commit to a platform shift","cons":"Doesn't resolve the long-term hosting question; may surface a fix that's specific to today's symptom rather than tomorrow's class"},{"label":"(b) Migrate hosted routes only","pros":"Smaller blast radius than full migration; lets us evaluate Vercel on a subset; reversible per-route","cons":"Splits the app across two hosts; ops complexity (two dashboards, two deploys); env-var duplication risk"},{"label":"(c) Full Vercel migration","pros":"Single hosting story; first-class Next.js features (ISR, edge, image optimization); simplest mental model","cons":"Largest blast radius; harder to reverse if Vercel's pricing/limits surprise us; lock-in to Vercel-specific primitives"}],"recommendation":"Orchestrator's tentative lean is (a) bisect first — get the immediate symptom resolved, then make the platform choice with that data in hand. But this needs Misha's call.","blocking_input":"Misha picks (a), (b), or (c) — and if (b)/(c), authorizes the scoping work.","links":["(see branch: Vercel migration / hosted-routes decision)"]},"actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:05:46.354Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-questi-96ddb2403edd68b4a922a8cb98788cc4","type":"question-raised","node_id":"vercel-migration","item_id":"i-vercel-scope-doc","text":"Want me to scope the Vercel-migration comparison doc?","actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:05:48.466Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-detset-96ddb2403edd68b4a922a8cb98788cc4","type":"item-details-set","node_id":"vercel-migration","item_id":"i-vercel-scope-doc","details":{"description":"Before committing to (b) or (c), the orchestrator can produce a comparison doc (current host vs. Vercel: feature parity, cost model, ops surface, observability hooks, rollback story). The work is ~2-4 hours.","instructions":"Reply: yes / no / not-yet. If yes, the orchestrator will draft the doc and surface it as a follow-up item with the comparison filled in.","recommendation":"Worth doing IF Misha leans (b) or (c). Skip if (a) bisect-first.","blocking_input":"Misha's go/no-go on scoping the doc","links":["(see branch: Vercel migration / hosted-routes decision)"]},"actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:05:48.486Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-action-c3e3a9548e7785e0f03ac3f564e9849c","type":"action-added","node_id":"vercel-migration","item_id":"i-vercel-status-sub","text":"Subscribe to vercel-status.com so we get pinged on incidents","actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:05:50.552Z"}
{"event_id":"cte-detset-c3e3a9548e7785e0f03ac3f564e9849c","type":"item-details-set","node_id":"vercel-migration","item_id":"i-vercel-status-sub","details":{"description":"Independent of the migration decision, subscribing to Vercel status alerts is cheap insurance — if Vercel's hosted-routes platform is in our serving chain, we want a heads-up on incidents.","instructions":"Go to vercel-status.com → Subscribe to Updates → enter Misha's email or a shared inbox. Choose channels (Email / RSS / Slack webhook).","recommendation":"Email subscription to the on-call address; takes <60 seconds.","blocking_input":"Misha completes subscription (no follow-up needed — small task, fire-and-forget).","links":["(see branch: Vercel migration / hosted-routes decision)"]},"actor":"dispatch","ts":"2026-05-21T19:05:50.569Z"}
